<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 03 at 4:48PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Rockdale and
northwestern Newton Counties through 515 PM EDT...
At 448 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Conyers. This storm was
nearly stationary.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Conyers, Covington, Oxford, Lakeview Estates, Georgia International
Horse Park, Magnet, Almon, Milstead, Richardson Park and Oak Hill.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
